        "senderName": "NWS Amarillo TX",
        "headline": "Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 12 at 10:09PM CDT until June 12 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX",
        "description": "SVRAMA\n\nThe National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a\n\n* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...\nNorthwestern Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...\nWestern Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...\n\n* Until 1115 PM CDT.\n\n* At 1008 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line\nextending from 13 miles southwest of Ware to 7 miles northwest of\nRomero, moving southeast at 25 mph.\n\nHAZARD...70 mph wind gusts.\n\nSOURCE...Radar indicated.\n\nIMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile\nhomes, roofs, and outbuildings.\n\n* Locations impacted include...\nRomero.",
        "instruction": "For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a\nbuilding.\n\nTorrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to\nflash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.",
